1 pouch(es) Pancake Batter
15 grams Maple Syrup
100 grams Chocolate Chips
1 sachet(s) Ground Cinnamon
to taste Butter

Mix the pancake batter and chocolate chips with the cinnamon in an appropriately-sized bowl.
TIP: Reserve a few chocolate chips to create Christmas designs before serving.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a knob of butter.
Once hot, add 2 tbsp of batter to the pan until bubbles start to appear, then turn and cook for 1-2 mins.
Repeat the process with two-thirds of the batter.
Use the rest of the pancake mix to make smaller pancakes with 1 tbsp batter each.

Plate up larger pancakes with smaller pancakes arranged above to resemble snowmen.
Use reserved chocolate chips to make the eyes, buttons and scarf.
Design the snowman arms using maple syrup, then drizzle the remainder over the top.